
Ayd&lt;U+0131&gt;n Karabulut (born 25 January 1988, Berlin) is a Turkish-German footballer. He currently plays for Turkish Super Lig club Sivasspor.
Career
Ayd&lt;U+0131&gt;n had started his career in Hertha Berlin, one of the leading teams in German capital where he was born. After a while, he pulled the attention of Turkish national team scouts as a promising starlet. He had 5 caps for U-19 national team. He joined Be&lt;U+015F&gt;ikta&lt;U+015F&gt; January 2006. His contract came into force on 8 February 2006 which will expire in May 2010. Ayd&lt;U+0131&gt;n had several recent occasions on Turkcell Super League in first season mostly as a substitute player.
On 16 February 2008, he was on the line-up of team up against Ankaraspor where Ayd&lt;U+0131&gt;n assisted Nobre by his corner kick. Subsequently, he tried to find the net by his own again with a corner kick, however he was denied by the opponent keeper Seneck&lt;U+00FD&gt; after his direct curving shoot.1 He scored his first ever goal for Be&lt;U+015F&gt;ikta&lt;U+015F&gt; on 5 January 2008 in Fortis Turkey Cup group match against Diyarbak&lt;U+0131&gt;r B&lt;U+015E&gt;B.2 Ayd&lt;U+0131&gt;n kept playing as a substitute player for his team and scored his very first goal in Turkish League on a crucial encounter against Trabzonspor.3
Ayd&lt;U+0131&gt;n has joined capital city team Ankaraspor in summer 2009, in return of Erhan G&lt;U+00FC&gt;ven, who joined Be&lt;U+015F&gt;ikta&lt;U+015F&gt; as the new defender.4
On 6 September 2013, Karabulut left Elaz&lt;U+0131&gt;&lt;U+011F&gt;spor and joined fellow Super Lig side Sivasspor.5
